    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[EGRS75] Erd\\H{o}s, P. and Graham, R. L. and Ruzsa, I. Z. and Straus, E. G., On the prime factors of $(\\sp{2n}\\sb{n})$. Math. Comp. (1975), 83-92.",
      "remarks": "A problem of Erd\\H{o}s, Graham, Ruzsa, and Straus \\cite{EGRS75}, who believed there is 'no doubt' that the answer is yes. \n\nFor example $(87,88)$ and $(607,608)$. Those $n$ such that there exists some suitable $m>n$ are listed as A129515 in the OEIS. \n\nA triple of such $n$ for which $\\binom{2n}{n}$ all share the same set of prime divisors is $(10003,10004,10005)$. It is not known whether there are such pairs of the shape $(n,n+k)$ for every $k\\geq 1$."
    },
